ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: For undergrads, definitely. For grad students, if they are interested in learning how to transcribe non-Western music, it is definitely fantastic for fine tuning aural skills. I would just remind them that it is very popular and will have lots of undergrads.
I would recommend the course to another student as a way to expose them to these diverse musical systems.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I feel very comfortable tackling any kind of non-Western melodic material for transcription! Absolutely got out of the class what I wanted to!
